He is wearing a white navy headgear, with short sleeved top, short pants, long socks and shoes. He is standing in front of a house, with a tall bush behind him on the right of the photograph. metadata.sgcool_label_text: A variety of portraits of British soldiers that show them at leisure as well as two photographs of James Steele placing a wreath at a remembrance ceremony, this collection is part of the archive of James Steele, Royal Artillery (Field) who served in Malaya from January 1941-February 1942, when interned as a P.O.W at Changi until his release in October 1945.
